content.description: New home sales dropped in May despite builder incentives.
Goldman continues to advise investors to diversify for better returns.
Hot weather continues to test patience and power bills.
FedEx forecasts weak Q1 profit, shares fall after-hours.
Circle Internet stock drops after bearish price target.
Tesla robotaxi momentum slowed by technical hurdle.

outlook: Housing cools, markets show mixed signals, and heat weighs on consumers as analysts urge diversification amid tech volatility. But the overall markets and indexes continue to be resilient with the S&P500 playng with the idea of new all-time highs.
